When generating or suggesting terminal commands that involve package management, always use pnpm instead of npm.

- Use `pnpm install` instead of `npm install`.
- Use `pnpm update` instead of `npm update`.
- Use `pnpm prune` instead of `npm prune`.
- Use `pnpm run <script>` instead of `npm run <script>`. 
- use the folder `www` as the base directory before running any `pnpm` commands